RATIONALE: Adjuvant therapy given after surgery for early breast cancer may cause infertility.

 Assessing young women's attitudes and feelings about the risk of infertility may help improve the ability to plan effective treatment.

 PURPOSE: This clinical trial is studying young women's attitudes and feelings about the risk of infertility related to adjuvant therapy for stage I or stage II breast cancer.

